"script": "Venus looks like Earth's twin, but landing there is a death sentence. The moment a probe touches down, the atmosphere starts crushing it with 90 times the pressure at our sea level, the same force you'd feel a kilometer deep in the ocean. And it's not done. The air is a furnace hot enough to melt lead, around 900 degrees Fahrenheit, hotter than Mercury even though Venus sits farther from the Sun. Thick clouds of sulfuric acid eat at the metal. The toughest probes we ever sent survived barely two hours before Venus silenced them for good.",
